derivation.yuyuan_name: Middle English: probably from clamb, obsolete past tense of climb

entry.tran: (通常指手脚并用地)攀爬，攀登
entry.def: If you clamber somewhere, you climb there with difficulty, usually using your hands as well as your feet.
